snippet.textDisplay:
Look, if United are doing their jobs properly they SHOULD have scouting reports on multiple players for EVERY position in the team. They will be ranked in terms of how much we want them and when a Plan A target is out of the picture (for whatever reason), there will be a Plan B player, etc.
A team like United doesn't get to Jan 5th and suddenly think, 'that player is out of the question, let's go scout another.'
Any half-decent manager could look at our team and KNOW where money should be spent, AND they will have thorough scouting reports on players they want to bring in. If United don't buy, it's because of the Glasers/Woodward.
Lack of success on the field is the only way we'll get rid - sponsors will not pay top dollar for a second rate team, AND the value of the club will start to decrease.

snippet.textDisplay: I just read a Skysports article where Ole says "Lingards finding his best form". i dont know what games Ole is watching, or whether or not he has a backbone at all, but to even say that Lingard is worthy to wear a Utd shirt is mindblowing. Ole isnt a strong enough manager to pull players aside and sort them out. He cannot make the tough decisions when benching under performers. Its why he doesnt bench Rashford, or James, or de Gea. No, he cannot be expected to lead a club that needs a strong technical manager who can grab poor performers and sort them out or bench them. I am sad to see Ole in charge now, I had hoped for better but I wont believe any news on signings until I see them shaking the managers hand while in a Utd shirt.
